    "Further to this, however, the charging decision-making process ordinarily goes through several iterations involving many lawyers.",
    "In this sense, the benchmark to which we compare GPT-3.5's performance may be unreasonably high.",
    "Despite GPT-3.5 missing several of the violations included in the complaint, its overall analysis of the facts for the charges it determined correctly was good (though we can only evaluate this qualitatively), using the legal reasoning framework provided.",
    "This is consistent with Yu et al.'s (2022) findings that prompts including the IRAC legal reasoning framework produced good results.",
    "Finally, we expect these models' performance to improve as they incorporate more data."
